dollars annually to improve obsolete industries and repair roads 
and communications in east germany over the next five to 10 years 
much of the burden is expected to hurt the wealthy west german 
economy in the shortterm resulting in a rise in inflation a 
decline in the value of the powerful west mark and even new taxes 
but some officials have predicted that anything less than a 11 
conversion could cause a new exodus of east germans to the west 
east germanys collapsing economy and the nearly 500000 east 
germans who emigrated west since january 1989 were main factors in 
the revolt that ousted the hardline communist regime 
many say a straight 11 conversion is necessary to allow east 
german workers and elderly people living off savings accounts to 
maintain adequate living standards in a unified germany 
east germans currently depend on heavy government subsidies for 
housing food and employment the subsidies would be phased out in 
the new freemarket economy under unification 
because of its outmoded factories unemployment would also rise 
quickly 
on sunday in downtown east berlin thousands walked through the 
historic heart of the old city 
a 55yearold man in a wheelchair said he misses the old regime 
he receives a disability allowance cheap housing and buys beer 
for the equivalent of about 16 cents 
in the first world war all was lost in the second world war 
all was lost now even without a war all is lost said the man 
who would not identify himself 
others are angry that east germans may be consigned to 
secondclass status in a unified germany 
some people think that the east germans are stupid but were 
not said sabina plesser 20 a lot of people will be 
unemployed but it will only last a little while we will learn and 
things will get better 
