<TEXT>
rival christian forces clashed with 
artillery and tanks in east beirut and mountains to the northeast 
today setting fuel tanks ablaze in an inferno that threatened a 
liquor factorys alcohol stocks 
the fighting in the citys christian sector and fogshrouded 
kesrouan highlands broke out around midnight shredding a 
ceasefire brokered by vaticanbacked mediators only a few hours 
earlier 
one person was wounded by sniper fire in the fighting between 
rebel gen michel aouns 19000 troops and the lebanese forces 
militia led by samir geagea a police report said 
at least 839 people have been killed and 2290 wounded since 
jan30 when aoun attacked the militia in a bid to crush the main 
challenge to his authority in the 310squaremile christian enclave 
police said both sides pounded each others positions with 155mm 
howitzers tanks and multibarreled rocket launchers in the latest 
flareup 
the shelling set fire to fuel tanks in the aouncontrolled area 
of jal eldib in east beirut before dawn turning the night sky red 
as flames shot up over the christian enclave 
the fire threatened to engulf a nearby factory that makes arak 
a licoriceflavored pernodlike liquor that is lebanons national 
drink 
associated press photographer eddy tamerian said firefighters 
were battling to keep the blaze from reaching the factory but 
the fire is so big it could continue to rage for days 
witnesses said a dozen other fires burned in the christian 
enclave 
the shortlived ceasefire negotiated by a threeman committee 
of neutral christians on sunday was the 15th such truce since jan 
30 
so far neither side has been able to score a decisive victory 
but geageas forces control twothirds of the christian sector 
including the ports in beirut jounieh and byblos and all airfields 
aoun must secure at least one port to open a seaborne supply 
route hostile syrian troops and their moslem militia allies ring 
the christian sector on its landward sides 
sundays truce halted two days of fighting in which aoun tried 
in vain to break through the lebanese forces defenses in kesrouan 
and geageas east beirut strongholds in the ashrafiyeh and 
karantina districts 
beiruts leftist assafir daily quoted a source close to aoun as 
saying of the ceasefire the committee has failed there will 
be no more mediations 
police estimated that up to onethird of the 1 million 
christians living in the enclave have fled to safer areas since 
jan 30 those who remain in the battle zone seek to retain some 
semblance of normality 
salim abusamra and rita zgheib took advantage of sundays lull 
to get married in the aouncontrolled zalka area but they took no 
chances both wore flak jackets over their wedding outfits 
aoun has refused to recognize hrawi who was elected in november 
to implement an arab leaguebrokered peace plan and rejects the 
plan because it does not provide castiron guarantees of a syrian 
withdrawal from lebanon 
he considers the 40000 syrian troops deployed in lebanon under 
a 1976 arab league peacekeeping mandate an army of occupation 
but there have been signs that aoun his forces isolated is 
softening his antisyrian stand he confirmed a report in kuwaits 
alqabas newspaper friday that he told arab leaders he was ready to 
accept an amended peace accord 
he did not say how he wanted the treaty changed but he has said 
before his main concern remains getting the syrians out of lebanon 
previous mediation efforts have foundered 
hrawi 64 a maronite catholic like aoun and geagea dismissed 
aoun as interim prime minister and army commander in november but 
aoun refuses to step down 
