editorial director catherine cahan on the issue of access for the 
disabled in the workplace 
radio investigative reporting phil rogers of wbbmam in 
chicago for reports on security gaps at ohare international 
airport 
public service in television journalism networks and top40 
markets wititv in milwaukee for a report on the problems of 
teenage sexual activity and pregnancy 
public service in television journalism all other markets 
ksattv in san antonio texas for a story on the impact of uranium 
mning on karnes county texas 
television editorials ed quinn paul sands don lundy judy 
vance and john beatty of kgtv in san diego calif for three 
editorials on local topics it was the second year in a row that 
the kgtv editorial crew won the honor 
television investigative reporting mark feldstein reporter 
and diane sperrazza producer of wusatv in washington dc for 
their investigation of allegations of drug use by washington mayor 
marion barry 
research about journalism gregory gordon and ronald e cohen 
for down to the wire upis fight for survival their book on 
the recent history of the news service 
