for approval the nonreligious education its students receive 
new life baptist a fundamentalist church founded in 1977 began 
operating a school in 1981 to provide a religiously based education 
for the children of its members 
state law requires all private schools to offer in addition to 
any religious training a secular or nonreligious education 
comparable to that provided in public schools 
under state law the church was required to seek the approval of 
a local school committee for the schools academic program 
new life baptists leaders believe it is a sin to seek such 
state approval for the school 
