emergency funds but the transit authority refused to consider the 
offer because it didnt address longrange funding for the system 
the county legislature last week voted against a utility tax 
that would have provided 9 million annually toward operating the 
system 
the system cost 55 million a year to run and the costs werent 
covered by a combination of farebox revenues and grants from the 
county state and federal governments 
cuomo said sunday that until a longterm source is found there 
is nothing the state can do to help the governor said the erie 
county legislature had reneged on its pledge to find the longterm 
funds 
