the us embassy on monday denied 
allegations it tried to kidnap from jail an air force sergeant 
convicted of killing his wife 
us military efforts to gain custody of the man have angered 
dutch officials 
the controversy stems from an incident friday night when eight 
us enlisted men and officers came to the utrecht jail where staff 
sgt charles d short is housed the dutch high court was to rule 
on his extradition the same day 
the court later ruled against the us extradition request 
because short 34 of highwood ill could face the death penalty 
in the united states for the 1988 slaying 
the americans were spotted by prison guards who called the 
police reports said they were then told to leave 
the episode made frontpage news in several major dutch 
