disease was already at an advanced stage and he had been 
hospitalized before because of other infections easton said 
leukemia is a form of cancer in which abnormal cells can spread 
in the bone marrow preventing it from making normal blood cells 
this leaves the patient highly susceptible to serious infections 
anemia and bleeding a transplant replaces the patients defective 
marrow with healthy marrow 
easton said the mothers bone marrow removal operation had been 
scheduled for this morning with the transplant to be done in the 
afternoon the operation was filled with risks and the odds of 
mitchells recovery were 25 percent to 40 percent he said 
