development said he signed the waiver because it will help 
residents of rent subsidized housing earn extra income and will 
also help the census bureau secure a more accurate account of the 
number of lowincome rentsubsidized americans 
the census bureau hires the temporary workers to canvass homes 
in which residents did not return the 1990 census form received in 
the mail the temporary jobs pay up to 8 an hour 
hud and census bureau officials said hiring residents of 
subsidized housing complexes to canvass their neighbors should help 
provide a more accurate count the formulas for several hud grant 
programs are based on census information 
lowincome residents who receive rent subsidies generally pay a 
percentage of their income for rent the waiver signed by kemp 
would exempt any income from the census bureau temporary jobs from 
the rent calculation 
