kaiser permanente the nations largest 
health maintenance organization was hit by a strike monday by 
11000 nurses technicians and maintenance workers cutting 
services at hospitals and closing some clinics 
workers defied the recommendation of a union negotiating team 
and rejected a 44 million contract offer friday by a 
3067to1474 vote 
a sixhour negotiating session with a federal mediator ended 
saturday without an agreement between pasadenabased kaiser 
permanente and service employees international union local 399 
the companys offer includes a 5 percent to 6 percent pay raise 
in the first year and a 3 percent to 5 percent increase in the 
second and third years it also guarantees that employees wages 
are 3 percent higher than the average wage at 12 los angelesarea 
hospitals used as a yardstick 
the union said 314 job classifications were affected it 
declined to outline its contract demands 
management knows what it will take to settle the strike 
said union vice president dave stilwell who said the topwage 
guarantee was simply no match for the work demands placed on kaiser 
employees 
