lava from kilauea volcano on monday 
flowed toward a subdivision of 83 homes in this coastal town and 
authorities ordered most of the residents to evacuate by nightfall 
the slowmoving flow was half a mile from kalapana gardens 
subdivision in the morning a lava flow in 1986 destroyed dozens of 
homes in the same area 
