parliament on march 28 enacted a 
press law abolishing censorship which was instituted after the 
sovietled invasion of 1968 
the move was among the latest by the noncommunist government 
which took office in december following a popular uprising to rid 
itself of four decades of communist control 
the law allows citizens to publish their own periodicals 
however deputies left intact a constitutional provision that 
radio television and the film industry controlled for decades by 
the communists are national property 
</TEXT>
