a county jury ruled march 26 that the 
houston chronicle did not libel a court reporter in a 1982 news 
story 
the jury said that seven out of eight contested sentences in the 
article were true or substantially true one time frame in the 
story was found to be incorrect but not libelous 
court reporter norma stewart sued eight years ago for more than 
2 million alleging that the article libeled her and damaged her 
reputation 
the article detailed the delay in setting an execution date for 
roger leroy degarmo convicted of the kidnapslaying of a houston 
medical technician 
degarmo has not been executed 
the article also discussed the delay in completing the trial 
transcript for automatic review by the texas court of criminal 
appeals 
