<TEXT>
as it moves toward a plebiscite on statehood 
next year puerto rico has an image problem many feel that 
prejudices against puerto ricans might dampen any enthusiasm in the 
us congress for the island to become the 51st state here then is 
a look at the gentler side of puerto rico a centuriesold culture 
rich in art music and tradition 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
one image of puerto ricans emerges 
from the graffitisprayed tenements of brooklyn and the bronx 
where poverty breeds street gangs drug dealers and welfare 
dependence 
but 1600 miles away on the caribbean island that generations 
of poor uneducated puerto ricans have fled you can find the other 
puerto rico 
the other puerto rico is 
old san juan a walled city founded by the explorer juan ponce 
de leon in the 1500s with narrow cobbled streets and 
pastelpainted colonial mansions 
the casals festival an annual series of classical music 
concerts started by the legendary spanish cellist pablo casals 
and the ponce museum of art which boasts one of the most 
extensive collections of italian baroque paintings in the americas 
the other puerto rico is the novels of manuel zenogandia and 
luis rafael sanchez the plays of rene marques the paintings of 
rafael tufino and lorenzo homar and the allpuerto rican movie lo 
que le paso a santiago santiago what happened to his new life 
nominated for an academy award as best foreignlanguage film of 
1989 
it is the tropical beat of salsa and merengue the minstrel folk 
tales of the jibaro mountain farmer religious wood carvings of 
saints known as santos fourstringed cuatro guitars and 
papiermache carnival masks with multiple devil horns 
it is a saturday night concert by the puerto rico symphony 
orchestra in the 3000seat performing arts center and a sunday 
afternoon guitar recital in la casa del libro the book house a 
littleknown museum of ancient manuscripts in old san juan 
it is what artist katherine harman harding who does abstract 
watercolors and collages found soon after arriving a year ago from 
indianapolis 
i moved here from the midwest and i see more art more 
progressive art done here than there including chicago she 
says 
im finding it to be an amazing place 
ricardo alegria director of the center for advanced studies of 
puerto rico and the caribbean which is housed in a beautifully 
restored 16th century convent in old san juan regards 
spanishspeaking puerto rico at least in cultural terms as a 
separate and older country than the united states 
puerto rico was already a country with grecoroman roots two 
centuries before the united states he says 
still the other puerto rico exists alongside the caribbean 
islands helterskelter commercial development widespread poverty 
and high levels of drugrelated crime and aids among 33 million 
people crowded onto an area only 100 miles long by 35 miles wide 
moreover the islands image is blurred by west side story 
stereotypes of the 25 million puerto ricans living in the 
crumbling urban barrios of the united states 
west side story was a beautiful musical but a very bad thing 
for puerto rico because it gave the wrong impression of puerto 
rico says former gov luis ferre the 86yearold father of 
puerto ricos statehood movement and multimillionaire benefactor of 
the impressive ponce museum of art in the southern coastal city of 
ponce his birthplace 
with the island planning a plebiscite in 1991 on whether to 
remain a us commonwealth form an independent nation or become 
the 51st state some feel prejudices against puerto ricans could 
dampen any enthusiasm for statehood in the us congress 
sure its a problem for us says former gov carlos romero 
barcelo leader of the prostatehood new progressive party its 
a problem for mississippi the image the nation has of 
mississippi 
he says polls have shown twothirds of americans would be 
willing to accept puerto rico as a state if the island favored it 
but if puerto ricans wanted independence 80 percent say they would 
accept that 
theres an underlying prejudice somewhere there he says 
puerto ricans of course have distinguished themselves in many 
fields in the united states singer jose feliciano film stars 
raul julia and rita moreno baseballs late roberto clemente and 
surgeon generaldesignate antonia novello to name a few 
