<TEXT>
christopher columbus discovered 
puerto rico on nov 14 1493 at the time the caribbean island was 
inhabited by aboriginal taino indians who called their land 
borinquen 
columbus companion juan ponce de leon seeker of the mythical 
fountain of perpetual youth established the first spanish 
settlement near san juan harbor in 1508 
spain imported african slaves to work sugar plantations and used 
puerto rico as a way station for goldladen ships from mexico to 
stock up on provisions before continuing their voyage to spain 
in 1898 spain ceded puerto rico along with guam and the 
philippines to the united states at the end of the 
spanishamerican war which was fought to liberate cuba from 
spanish rule 
puerto ricans became us citizens in 1917 and elected a 
governor for the first time in 1948 
the island became a us commonwealth in 1952 the status 
ratified by referendum in 1967 gives puerto ricans most rights and 
benefits of citizenship but they pay no federal taxes and cannot 
vote for us president puerto rico is represented in congress by 
one nonvoting delegate 
congress is now considering the islands proposal for a 
plebiscite in june 1991 on whether to remain a commonwealth with 
increased autonomy form an independent nation or become the 51st 
state 
puerto ricos relationship with the united states has been 
marred by occasional proindependence violence 
</TEXT>
