the beaches and mountains still attract millions of americas 
vacationing families but the high seas are luring a growing share 
of the nations travelers 
according to travel industry observers the number of families 
among the more than 35 million americans who take cruises annually 
has increased dramatically 
the most important reason is the price says bob dickinson 
senior vicepresident of sales and marketing for carnival cruise 
lines 
special rates for children has made cruising one of the most 
affordable and relaxing ways for families to take a vacation he 
notes adding that for families with infants his companys ships 
are equipped with cribs and high chairs and babysitting is 
available at a nominal charge 
according to dickinson several cruise lines have developed a 
special onboard schedule of activities especially for children 
on carnival cruises for example events geared toward ages 412 
might include a scavenger hunt a shipdrawing contest and a soft 
drink party with the captain 
a teen schedule might feature a name that tune contest or 
teen trivia contest pingpong tournament and disco party 
dickinson says all onboard facilities including discos video 
game rooms and swimming pools are available to younger passengers 
as well as a playroom which serves as their own gathering place 
youngsters especially enjoy kite flying bingo and movie time 
he adds explaining 
we find that many of them like participating in our programs 
more than any other aspect of the cruise and quite often prefer 
to stay on board rather than go ashore at the various ports of 
call 
programs for children ages 612 are offered by the norwegian 
cruise line on board its fleet of six ships on some of the ships 
