there are packages for traveling in relatively uncharted 
territory in south africa including one 17day tour that crosses 
the worlds oldest desert for sightings of rare desert elephants or 
5000yearold rock engravings before moving into bushmanland to 
make contact with some of the remaining little people travel 
is by allterrain vehicles carrying supplies and camping equipment 
according to the south african tourism board other trips include a 
photo tour of littlevisited areas in the northern area of kruger 
national park known for its elephant herds or rangerled trail 
walks in the park lasting three or four days 
tanzania and kenya expeditions are offered by the los 
angelesbased tusker trail amp safari co travel is by 
fourwheeldrive vehicles and most accommodation is under tent 
canvas though the kenya safari climbing through the foothills of 
mount kenya stops at the mount kenya safari club the tanzania 
trip includes exploration of the serengeti wildlife reserve and the 
tarangire national park 
rafting the katun river in siberia for two weeks and camping out 
in a wilderness encompassing glacial valleys steep gorges and 
forested canyons is possible through a tour organized by prescott 
mallory howe of huntington ny participants who must be in good 
physical shape and able to swim will learn rafting skills and meet 
the people of some remote siberian villages some of whom have 
never seen americans before the trips are arranged under a 
sovietamerican exchange program called project raft 
an outfit called idaho afloat takes the rough edge off river 
journeys and camping along the snake river many people were put 
off by the idea of camping trips as they were viewed as 
experiences on which one has to rough it says scott fasken 
owneroperator of the tour service his 22foot cargo raft comes 
equipped with kitchen and gear for deluxe camping along the way 
including tables chairs and large guest tents fasken adds that 
his guides take special care to teach children about the wildlife 
and history of hells canyon and lead them on hikes to explore 
archaeological remains indian burial sites and abandoned 
homesteads meanwhile parents can divert themselves with hiking 
swimming photography or whatever else they choose idaho afloat is 
based in grangeville idaho 
