<TEXT>
owners of nearly 15 million timeshare condominiums rent out 
their units without profit according to a survey commissioned by 
the resort property owners association 
weve known for years that consumer owners have been renting 
their property for peanuts what we didnt know until this survey 
was that the majority of consumer owners are renting these luxury 
condos or villas for as little as 40 to 110 per night says 
clinton burr rpoa president 
the survey shows that 60 percent of consumer owners rent out 
their condos at between 250 and 750 per week and 65 percent of 
these vacation condos are priced below hotel room rates in their 
communities this means that condo rentals in the most expensive 
resort communities like hawaii vail and palm springs have average 
rental rates less than 100 a night for a one or twobedroom condo 
with a kitchen travel agents and vacationers should consider condo 
rentals when planning a vacation says burr 
despite the low return 38 percent of the owners said they were 
satisfied and another 23 percent said they were very 
satisfied with property ownership 
