<TEXT>
here are some important factors to consider 
when shopping for medigap insurance as suggested by the senate 
special committee on aging 
review medicares gaps in coverage to determine what is 
important to you in a supplement consider policy features 
premiums waiting periods preexisting condition exclusions and 
maximum benefit clauses 
work with hometown agents and companies you know a company 
must meet certain qualifications to do business in your state 
talk with friends who have had good claims experiences 
investigate group insurance sold by legitimate organizations 
but remember some senior citizen or retired person organizations 
are legitimate and some are set up as fronts to get your business 
while some of these plans are good deals others are not as good as 
individual plans 
take into consideration any other coverage you have that 
continues beyond age 65 
consider how much you can afford to pay for hospital or 
medical bills and how much you can afford for supplemental health 
insurance premiums 
as a general rule buy one good comprehensive medicare 
supplemental policy there are some exceptions if you have an 
employer group policy that is affordable but limited in benefits 
check for special circumstances for which the insurance 
company may eliminate coverage for a health condition you had 
before you bought the policy a policy may refer to this as a 
preexisting condition 
beware of replacing existing coverage be suspicious of a 
suggestion that you give up any policy and buy a replacement often 
new policies will impose a waiting period or will have exclusions 
and waiting periods for preexisting conditions this means you may 
have to wait for up to six months before you will be eligible to 
collect anything on a new policy 
beware of maximum benefits most policies have a limit on 
benefits that may be expressed in dollars available or the number 
of days for which payments will be made 
check your right to renew beware of policies that let the 
company refuse to renew your policy on an individual basis a 
policy that is guaranteed renewable is preferable 
remember policies to supplement medicare are neither sold nor 
serviced by state or federal governments do not believe statements 
that insurance to supplement medicare is governmentsponsored 
dont pay cash write a check or money order payable to the 
company not the agent 
keep the agents andor companies names addresses and 
telephone numbers so that you can contact them easily in case of 
problems 
the medigap insurance market is highly competitve take your 
time do not let a shortterm enrollment period pressure you and 
remember that some states prohibit special enrollment periods 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
editors copies of a guide to purchasing medigap and longterm 
care insurance may be obtained by writing to the senate special 
committee on aging g31 dirksen building united states senate 
washington dc 20510 attention publications 
