a report from the american association of 
retired persons has been published to help people who need a 
hearing aid 
far too many people allow a hearing loss to limit their 
lives said aarp executive director horace b deets the 
purchase of a hearing aid can make a tremendous difference 
the first step the report says is to visit a doctor hearing 
loss can be a symptom of a treatable problem such as diabetes and 
a hearing aid could mask that problem 
hearing aids are sold by physicians audiologists and hearing 
aid dealers and there are three kinds of hearing aids 
behindtheear models those that go in the ear and those that fit 
in the ear canal 
prices range from 500 to 2000 
the aarp report considers the anatomy of the ear and causes of 
hearing loss what to consider when seeing a specialist questions 
to ask about hearing aids and other sources of information 
