previous rounds of discussions on structural barriers produced 
little progress both sides must produce an interim report by 
midapril and a final report before the sevennation economic 
summit to be held this year in houston in july 
the structural impediments discussions are just one of a set of 
trade negotiations currently underway with japan the japanese are 
facing a june 16 deadline to open up markets in three specific 
product areas satellites supercomputers and lumber or risk 
economic retaliation by the bush administration 
