<TEXT>
an index measuring the typical american 
familys ability to buy a house increased in february as lower 
prices and rising income offset higher mortgage rates a real 
estate trade group said monday 
the national association of realtors said its index rose to 
1051 in february meaning that a family with a median income of 
33816 had 1051 percent of the income needed to buy a 
medianpriced existing home costing 95400 
the median means half of the families earn more and half less 
or that half of the houses sell for more and half for less 
the index measured 1082 in december but slipped to 1042 in 
january 
the february increase in overall affordability conditions in 
part reflects the lowerpriced homes frequently available during 
the winter months said nar president norman d flynn 
although the lower median home price and rise in family income 
last month had a favorable impact on affordability conditions the 
index would have been stronger if mortgage interest rates had 
remained unchanged he added 
the median price for a house dropped 900 from januarys 96300 
while median family income was up 108 from 33708 the previous 
month the realtors group said the income needed to qualify for a 
loan on the typical home dropped 192 to 32160 
the interest rate used to compute the index however rose from 
97 percent in january to 1004 percent in february the realtors 
said the association uses a composite rate reflecting both 
fixedrate and adjustablerate mortgages 
the changes lowered the monthly principal and interest payment 
on a medianpriced home by 2 to 672 in february the payment 
represents 238 percent of the median familys income 
flynn said that while overall affordability remains favorable 
entrylevel buyers face difficulties 
these individuals are at a disadvantage in that they often 
cant save enough money for a downpayment and lack any home equity 
buildup to leverage a home purchase he said 
under februarys affordability conditions a family earning 
20000 would have sufficient income to qualify for a 59300 home 
using a 47400 loan a family earning 30000 would qualify for a 
88900 home with a 71100 loan 
the realtors said a family earning 40000 would have sufficent 
income to qualify for a 118500 home with a 94800 loan and a 
family with a 50000 income would qualify for a 148100 home 
using a 118500 loan 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

