dollars in the red 
los angelesbased first executive became the second southern 
california institution in as many days to be buried beneath an 
avalanche of losses from uninsured junk bonds which pay high rates 
because they fund risky ventures 
on sunday columbia savings amp loan association reported losses 
of 575 million in a fivemonth period due to junk bonds rendering 
it insolvent and in danger of seizure by federal regulators 
