of the nations hog herd 
released friday after trading ended the report said the hog 
herd as of march 1 was 4 percent smaller than on the same date a 
year earlier the market had expected a decline of closer to 26 
percent 
the governments estimate of the number of animals kept by 
producers for breeding purposes during the decemberfebruary 
quarter was also below market expectations 
the report suggested pork producers remain cautious about 
expanding their herds despite higher hog prices and that the 1990 
us hog herd will remain smaller than last years all year long 
