been tallied for the secret weekend balloting at union offices in 
six cities 
the sixmonth agreement retroactive to march 1 gives working 
union pilots 25 percent pay cuts increased health insurance 
contributions continuation of increased work hours imposed because 
of the unions strike and reduces easterns contributions to the 
employees retirement funds 
the concessions were part of easterns plan for emerging from 
chapter 11 bankruptcy protection the airline faces mounting 
skepticism from unsecured creditors who last week discussed 
calling for liquidation after eastern said it couldnt repay them 
50 cents on the dollar as agreed earlier 
once again the eastern pilots are offering to help ashby 
said this vote by no means says there is labor peace on the 
property we are very concerned about the future 
the two sides are in federally mediated talks on a permanent 
agreement 
the pilots say theyre willing to make concessions but eastern 
management must commit to hire more pilots back and to making 
miamibased eastern viable 
this concessionary agreement will not save eastern airlines 
its just a drop in the bucket ashby said 
eastern has some 1800 pilots more than half hired after the 
pilots union walked out march 4 1989 in sympathy with the 
